quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  106,1,"Since the Quraysh became accustomed,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  106,2,"accustomed to the journey of winter and summer,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  106,3,"therefore, let them worship the Lord of this House;"{1},footnotes:1:1
  106,4,"Who fed them against hunger, and secured them against fear."{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  107,1,"Did you see him who gives the lie to the Reward and Punishment of the Hereafter?"{1}{2}{3},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2,footnotes:3:3
  107,2,"Such is the one who repulses the orphans away,"{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  107,3,"and urges not the feeding of the needy."{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  107,4,"Woe, then, to those who pray,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  107,5,"but are heedless in their Prayers,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  107,6,"those who do good (in order) to be seen,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  107,7,"and deny people the articles of common necessity."{1},footnotes:1:1
  108,1,"(O Prophet), We have surely bestowed upon you good in abundance."{1},footnotes:1:1
  108,2,"So offer Prayer and sacrifice to your Lord alone."{1},footnotes:1:1
  108,3,"Verily your enemy alone has been cut off from the roots."{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2